  <h1>What Is LeadsMiner Pro? An Independent, Research-Based Review</h1>

  <p><strong>LeadsMiner Pro</strong> is a desktop automation tool built by Wayne Crowe — the same person behind the OLSP System and OLSP Academy — that automates the process of sending Facebook friend requests to targeted users in a chosen niche. Based on publicly available marketing pages and third-party commentary, our short take is this: the core concept of targeting people who already engage in your niche is a legitimate organic prospecting approach, and the one-time pricing is competitive. However, the tool automates activity that Facebook's Terms of Service generally prohibit for non-Meta-authorized applications, which creates a genuine account-restriction risk that the marketing materials significantly downplay. All earnings figures cited in promotional content are self-reported and unverified.</p>

  <VerdictBox>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> people already active in a specific Facebook niche who want to systematise their outreach, are comfortable accepting account-restriction risk from non-Meta-authorized automation, and intend to test the front-end product before committing to any upsells.</p>
    <p><strong>Not ideal for:</strong> anyone who cannot afford to risk their primary Facebook account, people who need a verified earnings track record before buying, or anyone expecting a complete "done-for-you" income system — this is a prospecting tool, not a standalone business model.</p>
  </VerdictBox>

  <h3>What Is It, and Who Is It For?</h3>
  <p>LeadsMiner Pro is positioned as a Facebook lead-generation accelerator for affiliate marketers, network marketers, coaches, and small businesses who want to grow a niche audience without paying for advertising. The central mechanic is automating the friend-request process: instead of manually browsing Facebook posts and groups to find engaged prospects, the software does the scanning and connecting on the user's behalf. It is aimed at people who already understand Facebook-based marketing and want to operate at greater scale than is practical by hand.</p>

